CSS Day 5: Flexbox (Most Important CSS Topic)

Flexbox is the most commonly used CSS layout system in modern web development.

It is used to:

Align items
Create responsive layouts
Build navigation bars
Display cards in rows
Center elements

React applications use Flexbox extensively.

What is Flexbox?

Without Flexbox:

Java
React
Spring Boot

Everything appears one below another.

With Flexbox:

Java    React    Spring Boot

Items are arranged in a row.

1. Enable Flexbox

To use Flexbox:

.container {
    display: flex;
}
HTML
<div class="container">
    <div class="box">Java</div>
    <div class="box">React</div>
    <div class="box">Spring Boot</div>
</div>
CSS
.container {
    display: flex;
}

.box {
    width: 150px;
    height: 80px;
    border: 2px solid black;
}

