3. align-items

Controls vertical alignment.

Example:

.container {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    height: 300px;
}

Values:

align-items: flex-start;
align-items: center;
align-items: flex-end;
4. gap

Adds space between flex items.

.container {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
}

Output:

[Java]    [React]    [Spring Boot]
5. flex-direction

Changes the direction of items.

Row (Default)
.container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
}

Output:

Java React Spring Boot
Column
.container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
}

